`SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` was deprecated in Android 11 (API 30) and is no longer honored. The modern fix is to react to **window insets** so your layout adjusts when the IME (keyboard) appears.

### Recommended approach — handle IME insets on Android

In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Let the app draw behind the keyboard area
        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);

        // React to keyboard insets
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
            Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!,
            new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var sysBarInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());

            // Use the larger of IME or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottomPadding = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, sysBarInsets.Bottom);
            view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottomPadding);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

### Why this works

| Old way (deprecated) | New way |
|---|---|
| `AdjustResize` told the OS to shrink your window | `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` tells *you* how tall the keyboard is |
| Broke in API 30+ | Works on all supported API levels via AndroidX compat |

### Quick alternative

If you just need basic behavior and don't need pixel-perfect control, `AdjustPan` still works — it scrolls the entire window up so the focused field is visible:

```csharp
// In Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs
Window!.SetSoftInputMode(SoftInput.AdjustPan);
```

But the insets approach is preferred because it only adjusts the bottom padding, keeping your toolbar/header pinned at the top.
